{
  "stem": "13313.3",
  "chunk_idx": 14,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my father somehow, again, through some like letter smuggling I think, knew the address where my mother was hidden and he found it.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he appeared in my mother's place after stalking the place for a few days and waiting for a safe moment.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I think my mother used to have her sister that I mentioned, also hidden nearby, Rosa, who didn't have a husband.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I think they had divorced, her husband had left.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And my mother used to take-- my mother had the money in the family.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The others were poor.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Used  to take supplies and money at least once a week.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So my father, in the night, stalked the place till he saw my mother, and then he we reunited with my mother.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So now my father and mother are together.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Wonderful.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Hidden in that same place.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And all this happened between the time that we were-- we had planned to go  and visit my mother.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So if nothing had changed we would have seen both my father and my mother.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Unfortunately, a week later, my mother, on one of her little trips to the building where my aunt was hidden, happened to walk in there exactly when there was a raid on the house.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Somebody [? else ?] [? told. ?] And all the Jews in that building were arrested and my mother as well.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "My mother was taken to a camp.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So my father escaped from a camp, finds my mother, and a week later my mother gets caught.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And this is how I turned out, it turned out to see my father and not my mother.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Where was your mother sent when she was arrested?",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
